<html><head><meta name="color-scheme" content="light dark"><meta charset="utf-8"></head><body><pre>{"id":1551,"date":"2024-07-31T23:55:00","date_gmt":"2024-07-31T13:55:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/?p=1551"},"modified":"2025-09-27T15:00:11","modified_gmt":"2025-09-27T05:00:11","slug":"the-climate-wars-mean-class-war","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/the-climate-wars-mean-class-war\/","title":{"rendered":"The Climate Wars Mean Class War"},"content":{"rendered":"\n&lt;p&gt;We are deep into a dangerous crisis, a crisis so massive, there are few means by which to fight, mitigate, and survive world-wide catastrophic climate events. Such events are occurring with increasing regularity and ferociousness. The capitalist class and its ruling elite have been selling us a lie that it\u2019s our fault we are in this crisis because of the individual choices we make and that it\u2019s the accumulation of these choices that are generating greenhouse gases. The catastrophes continue to escalate and we are losing.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;The dominant ideology of individualised responsibility has led to world-wide passivity in the face of impending global ecological and societal collapse. Passivity leads to blaming others for the problem and living in hope that someone else will fix it. As governments argue over meaningless zero emission targets, kicking the can further down the road, they are paying corporations globally to extract more fossil fuels and accelerate greenhouse gas emissions.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;The statistics are clear as to how we have been plunged into this mess. Carbon Majors, a database operated by not-for-profit think tank Influence Map, tracked 122 of the world\u2019s largest oil, gas, coal and cement producers to quantify the production-linked operational emissions and emissions from the combustion or use of their products. The Carbon Majors database also traced cumulative emissions from 1854 to 2022 of these 122 companies. They found that they are responsible for 72% of global fossil fuel and cement CO2 emissions since 1751. Furthermore, 70% of these global CO2 emissions can be attributed to just 78 corporate and state producing entities.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;There can be no faith in parliament to act. In Australia, climate deniers are now supporting costly and dangerous nuclear energy that generates waste materials that remain lethal for up to 200,000 years. The more \u201cprogressive\u201d capitalists are, for the most part, both half-hearted in their plans and just as committed to top-down planning and profit maximisation. Their renewable energy projects are imposed from the outside, rather than being community-led, and are easy prey for right wing activists advancing bad faith opposition. They subsidise electric vehicles rather than moving to a truly sustainable transport system where the private car occupies a small residual place.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;The wider shift towards batteries is being done without addressing the environmental effects of the mining industry, so damage from coal, oil and gas extraction is to be replaced by damage from nickel and lithium mining. In the struggle between the different factions of capital, saving the world from climate change comes a distant second behind the continued maximisation of profit and the maintenance of the capitalists\u2019 control.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div class=\"wp-block-image\"&gt;\n&lt;figure class=\"aligncenter size-medium\"&gt;&lt;img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" src=\"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/School-strikes-for-climate-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"The School Strike 4 climate march 2015. One sign reads, &amp;quot;#STOP ADANI&amp;quot;.\" class=\"wp-image-1557\" srcset=\"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/School-strikes-for-climate-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/School-strikes-for-climate-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/School-strikes-for-climate.jpg 800w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/&gt;&lt;figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"&gt;Image by Stephen Hass&lt;\/figcaption&gt;&lt;\/figure&gt;\n&lt;\/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;Capitalism is a class system. A system that sees a small ruling capitalist elite in control on the one hand and the mass of the people controlled, on the other, separated by force from controlling their own productive work. These people, the overwhelming majority, the working class, have one means of survival, to work for the capitalists for wages to buy their means to live. The domination of the ruling capitalist class is guaranteed by the power of the state, which exists for precisely that purpose. The very real threat to the health and safety of all workers is because the capitalists refuse any solution which would negatively affect their interests.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p class=\"has-text-align-center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Climate Wars Mean Class War!&lt;\/strong&gt;&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;Our struggle must be global. Our interests are the same as all workers across the globe. We all face catastrophe caused by capitalism. The working class has no country: we have a whole planet. We, the workers, need to act quickly to avert the inevitability of catastrophe if things continue as they are. This means asserting our collective power to paralyse the capitalist doomsday machine.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;It is in the workplace that we have the ability to act for ourselves, without delegating control to capitalist politicians. And it is in the workplace we have the ability to take power away from the capitalists and wield it ourselves. In the struggle for the immediate goal of survival, we will find it necessary to end capitalism and establish our collective freedom. By abolishing the profit system, we can reconcile the requirement for producing the goods and services necessary for a civilised life with the necessity to live sustainably within our natural environment. We must have a just transition for all, whether it\u2019s workers in fossil fuel industries, local communities currently on the edge of viability, or anyone else. We have a world to save \u2013 and a world to win.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p class=\"has-text-align-center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NO WAR BUT CLASS WAR&lt;\/strong&gt;&lt;\/p&gt;\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"We are deep into a dangerous crisis, a crisis so massive, there are few means by which to fight, mitigate, and survive world-wide catastrophic climate events. \n&lt;a class=\"moretag\" href=\"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/the-climate-wars-mean-class-war\/\"&gt; [...]&lt;\/a&gt;","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1867,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_coblocks_attr":"","_coblocks_dimensions":"","_coblocks_responsive_height":"","_coblocks_accordion_ie_support":"","footnotes":""},"categories":[31,26,2],"tags":[52],"class_list":["post-1551","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-capitalism","category-climate","category-anvil","tag-climate"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1551","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1551"}],"version-history":[{"count":4,"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1551\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1568,"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1551\/revisions\/1568"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/1867"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=1551"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=1551"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=1551"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}</pre><div class="json-formatter-container"></div></body></html>